              <title>E4L interactive case studies [Gemma Towle: Presentation]</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3429</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3429</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>E4L interactive case studies</strong></p>
<p>Gemma Towle, (then) University of Northampton</p>
<p>PPT</p>
<p><strong>Presented in Members' Corner at ELESIG Symposium: Impact of Learner Experience research &ndash; Digital Literacies 20 Nov 2008</strong></p>
<p>Suite S1, Innovation Centre, Longbridge Technology Park, 1 Devon Way Birmingham B31</p>
<p>E4L is a project investigating learners' opinions and experiences.<br />Core themes - transitional periods, use of shadow technologies, lightbulb moments.<br />Looked at learners from ACT, HE and, most lately, FE</p>
<p>There are interactive case studies, themed and categorised video and audio of learners talking about their experiences, available freely online along with transcripts and the facility for comments, reflections and recommendations from peers. They are intended to be of use to fellow practitioners in evaluating the student experience.<br /><br /><a href="http://elesig.ning.com/forum/attachment/download?id=2007026:UploadedFi58:9383">http://ELESIG.ning.com/forum/attachment/download?id=2007026:UploadedFi58:9383</a></p>
